Provide your answer with these fields.
- explanation: your evaluation of the scenario provided by the agent A.
- is_report_correct: whether the report is correct or not (true/false). True means there is a violation.
</response format>
<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The pointer expression &pp[1] produces a char* that points immediately after the MHD_PostProcessor object. If the MHD_PostProcessor object was not allocated with trailing storage for the buffer (e.g. allocated only as sizeof(*pp) rather than sizeof(*pp) + buffer_size or using a flexible-array member), then accesses via buf (and any subsequent use by string.h routines such as strlen/strcpy/memcpy etc.) will read/write memory beyond the bounds of the object and thus violate MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17. The code is only safe when pp actually refers to an allocation that contains additional bytes immediately after the struct (and that buffer size is respected); absent that guarantee the rule is violated.
</scenario>

